title: Les Misérables, Vol. 1
creator: Victor Hugo
description: LibriVox recording of Les Misérables, Vol. 1, by Victor Hugo. Read by LibriVox volunteers. An ex-convict breaks parole and starts a new life as a righteous man, but is pursued by a police inspector. Along the way, the ex-convict joins a revolution, adopts a daughter, and beats people up. Hooray. (Summary by smileyman457) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; audiobook; steal; romance; ex-convict; French Revolution;
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: I understand the point of Librivox, but at the same time I think when listening to an audiobook I should be able to understand what I am hearing. I'm not here. There's a reader in this book of whose readings I cannot even distinguish individual words. Quite Unreal.
the voices were a little annoying and hard to understand at times, but ok...
And the readers did a good job.  I can't understand people complaining.  thank you again librivox.

I know Librivox is a volunteer program but there is no excuse to have audio that is so bad it cant be listened to. You don't donate broken stuff to Goodwill, you don't upload bad audio to Librivox.

I do appreciate the few recordings that are professional. What else is there to say? Its free.
reviews.reviewtitle: Great Book... but the recordings... meh
